review_blob: Beer club selection, Really liked the mahogany dark color, contrasted well with the 30 inch  Pepperoni Pie from 3 Brothers, Seaside Heights.

Beer club selection out of a variety pack ,  Roasted Champagne Malt, thats fancy . 
Would like to try more of this brewers offerings.

Beer club selection, surprisingly by a member who really didnt enjoy Estrella De Galicia, of which I am a great fan. This is lighter , crisper. Really enjoyed after a long surf.  Imagine it would be even better served on the shores of the Spanish coast.
Beer club selection: Served Poolside , Fruity Cloudy, Blue Moonish First 6 ounces better than the last.
Tall, smooth. Purchased for World Cup enjoyment. My supply ran out as did Schweinstegers . Definately my favorite German Pilsner.
Nice aroma, nice pour, mild hoppy bite at the end .Dont drink too many pale ales, but this one is recommended .
I was surprised by how dark it was, Id describe  the taste as someone did a shot of Jamesons then drank out of your glass.
Frederick is a nice little town, this is a nice little  porter.  Appealing brown color, I like the malt.
UPDATED: MAY 7, 2010

Beer club sampling. 
Appearance: Nice Pumpkin orange color
Not overly hoppy.
UPDATED: APR 28, 2010

From the name I thought it would go well with some pizza & carbonara.  Unfortunately it didnt work out, 
Too hoppy for me.

Aroma: Citurs , fresh , wonderful
Appearance, Golden
Too bad for the Taste: Too much like air freshener for me
Had a quick pint whie picking up takeout. Nice color, not overly hoppy. Cold, went down smooth, I enjoyed it,
UPDATED: JAN 7, 2010
Tasted like Bud or Henikenen , my two least favorite beers.  Probaly explains why none of the Poles were buying it at  the Bayway woeld of Liquors.
UPDATED: MAY 7, 2010

Served in a Kings Goblet. 

OK beer snobs, best beer I have ever had. 
Ice cold, ribs, mashed potatoes Wonderful.

Havent had an ice beer in more than a decade. Decent head, not too hoppy, nice color. 
Went down smooth. , eadache started an hour later.

Dark invting color, but for me thats where it ends, Too hoppy, bitter. 
IIm just not a fan of anything Sam Adams.

Skunky aroma,instant headache,  Great marketing though . 

For the best review please see crisp500, hes right on.

Why is this beer suddenly everywhere ? I even ran into it on tap at yankee Stadium. 
Nice fruity smell, comes across a bit sour for me after  a couple.

Had one in Morroco town at Epcot while watching the belly dancer with my kids. 
The show was ending and I didnt have time to make it to one of the better lands. Tasted like pondwater full of dirt &  sticks.  Maybe some grass too. I think its why dogs eat grass to make themselves vomit.
I prefer it without the large chunk of orange that is usually jammed on the rim . Enough of a fruity taste without the orange says Doug.

The first beer I ever had with fruit in it.  
Was it a lemon or orange ?
Might have to revisit this one.
I always thought this was coors light with red dye. Was it ? It seemed fashionable at the time.
Half and Half or Black & Tan. I enjoy  it with mixed company.  Forgettable when drank alone

Picked up a case of minis at Samss club last fall.  Didnt realize it was a dunkel. Now I have to find out what a dunkel is. Nice dark color, went down smooth watching Germany v Spain in the Euros with some Brats.

High school, anchorman, quarters .First vomit, first hangover . The Bud Mud. 
Doesnt even taste good at a baseball game. 
I do like the commercials though.

For years I went through these like there was no tomorrow. I even went to the brewery. The wide mouths, the seasonal baseball bat bottles. Ice cold there was nothing better, then one day I coulld drink them no more.  Ill give it a 2 out of respect.

Boom sha lock lock boom...
Afdter  couple Mickeys big mouths chaos always ensued. The stuff just made people crazy
Seemed to go well with the food of Costa Rica.  When not drinking Bavaria light , this was the ticket.
My light beer choice during my stay in CR.  Next time I go back will see if it still fits the bill.
Love the logo, bought a shirt & sticker though.   Didnt care for the beer though.  Preferred Pilsen.
Was given a six pack of cans from a co-worker.  Super light, probably very refreshing  under a palm tree after a nice session at Rincon . I think with this one its all about location.

Label should read, not to be consumed by those over the age of 21 or those not wearing a baja jacket that reads Spring Break 89

Summer in a bottle,  Refreshing, light 
the perfect companion to Cabo Wabo .

Oil cans used to seem soooo good , now they seem soooo bad. Still fun to shotgun though . 

Did the US always get this Canadian version? 

Blame Canada!

Japanese lager  by way of Canada, no way.  I do like the real thing. 
There are big ships capable of bringing us the real thing.

Tanaka of Tokyo, Hawaii, sampled the Japanese version. Wonderful, crisp , dry. 

Molson variety , not so good. Will only drink again when the real thing is available.

My favorite faux japanese beer, made by Bud but doesnt taste like bud. 

Goes down smooth at Arrirang.

Lo mein, Fried Rice, Dumplings, Sweet & Sour, Chow Mein, Beef with Broccoli, Chicken with cashews...

MMMMMMmmmmm

I think I still have spare ribs stuck in my tooth.
UPDATED: NOV 15, 2009

I  remember having my first Icehouse. A dimly lit Bowling Alley in  Tempe, 1994.  The bartender waived us over to him as if he was going to tell us some big secret. He whispers, "Try this, it just came in , I served it on league night.It got out of hand."

That was good enough for me.

This beer is still made.... Really ?  Did anyone ever buy it ? 
I remember the can, Thankfully, I dont t remember the taste .
UPDATED: APR 28, 2010

Fine tasting beer,I have no issues with it.  But it doesnt scream Mexico to me, when Im feeling South of the Border.   The only time I drink it is part of the "Beers of Mexico" case at  Sams Club  & it always is finished after the XX Amber, Tecate & Sol that accompany it in the box.
